dec $is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')

1. Case analysis on typeIR''

  1. Case (% has type boolTypeIR)

    1. (Let boolTypeIR be (typeIR'' as boolTypeIR))

    2. If ((boolTypeIR matches pattern `BOOL`)), then

      1. Return true

    2. Else Phantom#95

  2. Case (% has type errorTypeIR)

    1. (Let errorTypeIR be (typeIR'' as errorTypeIR))

    2. If ((errorTypeIR matches pattern `ERROR`)), then

      1. Return true

    2. Else Phantom#96

  3. Case (% has type stringTypeIR)

    1. (Let stringTypeIR be (typeIR'' as stringTypeIR))

    2. If ((stringTypeIR matches pattern `STRING`)), then

      1. Return true

    2. Else Phantom#97

  4. Case (% has type integerTypeIR)

    1. (Let integerTypeIR be (typeIR'' as integerTypeIR))

    2. Return true

  5. Case (% has type typedefTypeIR)

    1. (Let (typedef _typeId typeIR'') be (typeIR'' as typedefTypeIR))

    2. Return $is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')

  6. Case (% has type newTypeIR)

    1. (Let (type _typeId typeIR'') be (typeIR'' as newTypeIR))

    2. Return $is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')

  7. Case (% has type tupleTypeIR)

    1. (Let (tuple < typeIR''* >) be (typeIR'' as tupleTypeIR))

    2. Return $forall_($is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')*)

  8. Case (% has type headerStackTypeIR)

    1. (Let (typeIR'' [ _nat ]) be (typeIR'' as headerStackTypeIR))

    2. Return $is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')

  9. Case (% has type structTypeIR)

    1. (Let (struct _typeId < _typeArgumentIR* > { (_annotationList typeIR'' _nameIR ;)* }) be (typeIR'' as structTypeIR))

    2. Return $forall_($is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')*)

  10. Case (% has type headerTypeIR)

    1. (Let (header _typeId < _typeArgumentIR* > { (_annotationList typeIR'' _nameIR ;)* }) be (typeIR'' as headerTypeIR))

    2. Return $forall_($is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')*)

  11. Case (% has type headerUnionTypeIR)

    1. (Let (header_union _typeId < _typeArgumentIR* > { (_annotationList typeIR'' _nameIR ;)* }) be (typeIR'' as headerUnionTypeIR))

    2. Return $forall_($is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')*)

  12. Case (% has type simpleEnumTypeIR)

    1. (Let (enum _typeId { _nameIR* }) be (typeIR'' as simpleEnumTypeIR))

    2. Return true

  13. Case (% has type serializableEnumTypeIR)

    1. (Let (enum _typeId < typeIR'' > { _valueFieldIR* }) be (typeIR'' as serializableEnumTypeIR))

    2. Return $is_defaultable_typeIR(typeIR'')

1. Else Phantom#98

2. Return false

