        2. Else Phantom#1745

  8. Case (% has type breakStatementIR)

    1. (Let breakStatementIR be (statementIR'' as breakStatementIR))

    2. Result in IC', STO', (breakStatementIR as statementIR)

  9. Case (% has type continueStatementIR)

    1. (Let continueStatementIR be (statementIR'' as continueStatementIR))

    2. Result in IC', STO', (continueStatementIR as statementIR)

  10. Case (% has type switchStatementIR)

    1. (Let (switch ( typedExpressionIR ) { switchCaseListIR }) be (statementIR'' as switchStatementIR))

    2. (SwitchCases_inst: p' IC' STO' |- switchCaseListIR : STO_1 switchCaseListIR_inst)

    3. Result in IC', STO_1, ((switch ( typedExpressionIR ) { switchCaseListIR_inst }) as statementIR)

1. Else Phantom#1746

2. If ((p' matches pattern `LOCAL`)), then

  1. Case analysis on statementIR''

    1. Case (% has type returnStatementIR)

      1. (Let returnStatementIR be (statementIR'' as returnStatementIR))

      2. Result in IC', STO', (returnStatementIR as statementIR)

    2. Case (% has type blockStatementIR)

      1. (Let (annotationList { blockElementStatementListIR }) be (statementIR'' as blockStatementIR))

      2. (Let IC_1 be $enter_i(IC'))

